		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200393</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Audion secured $15 million in a Series B round, putting the company in a prime position to disrupt the world&#8217;s audio ad market through AI. This funding comes at a</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/audion-raises-15m-to-expand-audio-advertising-tech/" data-wpel-link="internal">Audion Raises $15M to Expand Audio Advertising Tech</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://audionplayer.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Audion </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">secured $15 million in a Series B </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/nervonik-raises-52-5m-for-nerve-stim-tech/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">round</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, putting the company in a prime position to disrupt the world&#8217;s audio ad market through AI. This funding comes at a time when more brands are spending money on podcasts, digital radio and streaming services, looking for the performance data they get with display and search.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The round saw participation from a consortium of prominent investors, including Founders Future, Elevation Capital, and Bpifrance. This latest injection brings Audion’s total funding to approximately $22.6 million, signalling strong investor confidence in the company’s ability to automate and optimise the fragmented world of digital audio.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Solving the Fragmentation Problem</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Since its creation in 2018 by Arthur Larrey and Kamel El Hadef, Audion has been developing a technology infrastructure capable of tackling the difficulties of the fragmented landscape of contemporary audio consumption. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With audio content rather than visual, the audience and content are generally subject to large disbursement between platforms (Spotify, Apple Podcasts, YouTube, and digital radio station niches), preventing brands from running seamless, high-performance campaigns.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200394" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200394" class="size-large wp-image-200394" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Ad-1024x683.jpg" alt="Ad" width="1024" height="683" /><p id="caption-attachment-200394" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Audio is one of the oldest mediums, but it is currently undergoing its most significant reinvention,&#8221; said Arthur Larrey, co-founder and CEO of Audion. &#8220;With this funding, we are moving beyond simple ad placement to provide a full AI-driven performance engine. We are giving brands the tools to predict outcomes, not just buy impressions.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The centrepiece of this strategy is the recently launched Audion AI, a tool that uses specialised AI agents to translate a brand’s creative brief into a cross-platform strategy. The technology analyses the equivalent of nearly 100 years of audio and video content every month to understand contextual signals, ensuring ads are placed where they will be most effective.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/nervonik-raises-52-5m-for-nerve-stim-tech/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Nervonik Raises $52.5M for Nerve Stim Tech</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Strategic U.S. Expansion and Product Roadmap</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">While Audion currently operates out of European hubs including Paris, London, Milan, and Amsterdam, a primary objective for the new capital is an aggressive entry into the United States market. The U.S. represents the largest global market for podcasting and digital audio, offering a massive growth opportunity for Audion’s specialised AI solutions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Beyond geographical expansion, the company plans to accelerate the development of its Audion360 platform. For publishers and creators this end-to-end package offers a CMS for podcasts with built-in monetisation technology.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Audion seeks to narrow this divide between content providers and advertisers in the digital space so that the ROI from brand lift and drive-to-store campaigns is measurable in much the same way a click-through rate is.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Rise of Outcome-Driven Audio</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This move to performance-based audio is an age inevitable. As the industry sheds its reliance on 2005&#8217;s single-minded emphasis on &#8220;reach at all costs&#8221;, agencies and advertisers are now beginning to look for performance in their audio campaigns. Using a combination of Dynamic Creative Optimisation (DCO), Audion&#8217;s technology adapts the copy based on the time, place and performance history of the listener.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With 50-plus data experts and serving over 1500 brands, Audion is quickly transforming from an incipient startup to a serious player in the global AdTech market. The Series B fresh capital guarantees that they have the dry powder to give existing big brothers in the industry a run for their money.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/audion-raises-15m-to-expand-audio-advertising-tech/" data-wpel-link="internal">Audion Raises $15M to Expand Audio Advertising Tech</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
