		<link>https://ventureburn.com/nervonik-raises-52-5m-for-nerve-stim-tech/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 17:27:35 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200373</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Nervonik Inc., the Los Angeles-based clinical-stage bioelectronic medicine innovator, has announced the successful oversubscribed financing of a $52.5 million Series B led by Sofinnova Partners. This round represents a major</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/nervonik-raises-52-5m-for-nerve-stim-tech/" data-wpel-link="internal">Nervonik Raises $52.5M for Nerve Stim Tech</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://nervonik.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Nervonik Inc</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">., the Los Angeles-based clinical-stage bioelectronic medicine innovator, has announced the successful oversubscribed financing of a $52.5 million Series B led by Sofinnova Partners. This </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/sereact-raises-110m-to-scale-ai-robotics-platform/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">round </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">represents a major step forward in the company’s campaign to disrupt the peripheral nerve stimulation (PNS) space: developing a &#8216;smart&#8217; neuromodulation platform that adjusts according to live body signals.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The latest round was led by Amzak Health and was substantially oversubscribed by a syndicate of high-profile medical technology investors, including Elevage Medical Technologies, U.S. Venture Partners (USVP), Lumira Ventures, Foothill Ventures and Shangbay Capital. This most recent capital raise takes the total invested in Nervonik to in excess of $65 million following an early 2025 Series A of $13 million.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Solving the &#8220;Static&#8221; Stimulation Problem</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Although peripheral nerve stimulation has been around for decades as a non-opioid alternative to chronic pain, most conventional systems are limited by producing a static &#8220;one size fits all&#8221; electrical pulse. Once the body adapts or activity levels change, the therapy can result in reducing pain, necessitating manual reprogramming.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200374" style="width: 570px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200374" class="size-full wp-image-200374" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Nervonik.jpg" alt="Nervonik" width="560" height="238" /><p id="caption-attachment-200374" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Nervonik</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Nervonik&#8217;s built-in technology attempts to overcome this by embedding lab-tested, sophisticated sensing technology into the implantable leads. Now, not only can the device deliver its therapeutic electrical impulses to your nervous system, but it can also, utilizing recorded responses from your nerves, follow its response to the therapy and modify its delivery of electrical signals to optimize pain control in sleep, while walking, or when exercising.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“Nervonik is creating a uniquely differentiated neuromodulation platform,” said Aydin Babakhani, Nervonik CEO and founder. “This funding will allow us to grow our clinical programs and commercial capabilities while bringing an innovative, next-generation therapy to the patients who could benefit most.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/sereact-raises-110m-to-scale-ai-robotics-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Sereact Raises $110M to Scale AI Robotics Platform</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Commercialization and Clinical Expansion</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Series B proceeds are earmarked for several critical initiatives:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Clinical Trials</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Speed up current first-in-human studies that are underway to reinforce the effectiveness of ECAP-guided therapy.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Product Development</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Optimization of components within the wearable and implantable devices to allow for ease of use, comfort, and durability for the active lifestyle user.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Commercial Infrastructure</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Expanding the sales and marketing organizations in anticipation of a planned launch in the US.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The medical world has had a growing interest in PNS in an effort to fight off the opioid epidemic. Instead of putting systemic side effects into patients by medication, Nervonik&#8217;s targeted control technology is seeking to treat chronic pain at the source, the peripheral nerves, locally, reversibly, and now &#8220;intelligently&#8221;.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/nervonik-raises-52-5m-for-nerve-stim-tech/" data-wpel-link="internal">Nervonik Raises $52.5M for Nerve Stim Tech</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
