		<title>Kashable Raises $60M Series C Led by Goldman Sachs</title>
		<link>https://ventureburn.com/kashable-raises-60m-series-c-led-by-goldman-sachs/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ekemini]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 17:09:12 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[News]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Venture Capital]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ventureburn.com/?p=200369</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Kashable, the fintech trailblazer for issuing socially conscious credit as an employer-sponsored benefit, announced that it has secured $60 million in Series C financing. Led by Sustainable Investing at Goldman</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/kashable-raises-60m-series-c-led-by-goldman-sachs/" data-wpel-link="internal">Kashable Raises $60M Series C Led by Goldman Sachs</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://kashable.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Kashable</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, the fintech trailblazer for issuing socially conscious credit as an employer-sponsored benefit, announced that it has secured $60 million in Series C </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/sereact-raises-110m-to-scale-ai-robotics-platform/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">financing</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">. Led by Sustainable Investing at Goldman Sachs Alternatives and with the ongoing support of current investors Revolution Ventures and EJF Ventures,</span></p>
<p>According to the company, the funding is an important milestone for the firm headquartered in New York. The round comprises $25 million raised by Goldman Sachs Alternatives in the first instance. With an agreement to raise a further $25 million over the coming months, and $10 million from previous investors.</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Redefining Credit for the American Workforce</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Kashable was established in 2013, in Los Angeles, by co-CEOs Einat Steklov and Rishi Kumar. Kashable is uniquely positioned among a highly competitive fintech market. Instead of directly competing with consumer loans, the company works with the HR/payroll systems of employers to provide employees with low-cost loans. The repayment is made by deductions from the salary.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_200370" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200370" class="size-full wp-image-200370" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/Kashable.jpg" alt="Kashable" width="600" height="262" /><p id="caption-attachment-200370" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Kashable</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Kashable has a differentiated model to avoid high credit losses. </span>&#8220;Employer-sponsored financial wellness with access to credit enables us to support more of America&#8217;s hard-working citizens,&#8221; said Rishi Kumar. Kashable is now distributed to over 4 million people within hundreds of large companies, from government agencies to manufacturing companies.  It is a financial safety net for the middle market by providing an alternative to credit card debt.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/sereact-raises-110m-to-scale-ai-robotics-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Sereact Raises $110M to Scale AI Robotics Platform</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Strategic Validation and Growth</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Here, the involvement of Goldman Sachs Alternatives lends a prestigious confirmation of Kashable&#8217;s mission-driven business. </span>&#8220;Kashable would fit our mandate of investing in companies bringing liquidity and solutions to low-income communities,&#8217; said Greg Shell.</p>
<p>&#8220;They have experienced aggressive growth; the company has grown more than 40% annually as of early 2026.&#8221; &#8220;Kashable has underwritten close to $2 billion in loans and expects its 2026 volume may be greater than $500 million.&#8221; &#8220;This distinguishes it from many high-growth fintech companies due to its profitability over the years, making it attractive to institutional investors.&#8221;</p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Future Roadmap: Beyond Lending</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With $60 million in fresh capital, Kashable plans to:</span></p>
<ol>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Scale Employer Footprint</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Broaden to include additional Fortune 500s and government agencies.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Product Diversification</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Expand its suite of financial wellness tools, such as credit monitoring and financial coaching.</span></li>
<li class="yoast-text-mark" style="font-weight: 400">&gt;<b>Data Integration</b><span style="font-weight: 400">: Continue to enhance the company&#8217;s proprietary underwriting algorithms, which may allow the use of live payroll data instead of relying on traditional credit ratings.</span></li>
</ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/kashable-raises-60m-series-c-led-by-goldman-sachs/" data-wpel-link="internal">Kashable Raises $60M Series C Led by Goldman Sachs</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
			</item>
